            <hr>
            The government has promised to provide free HPV vaccine for ages 9-14 at primary health centres when consent has been provided by parents/guardians. If your parents choose to wait until you are older, they will need to make arrangements with your nurse if it is available when you are ready or pay for it.
        </p>
